ficial trailer was released for the album. The visual promotion, produced by Thorburn, was created as a homage to various [[B-Movie]] action films of the 1980s, as well as Thorburn's own [[Bad Biology]]. \n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column    = Producer(s)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.55127/title.r-a-the-rugged-man-unveils-all-my-heroes-are-dead-tracklist-drops-golden-oldies-with-slug |title=R.A. The Rugged Man Unveils 'All My Heroes Are Dead' Tracklist & Drops 'Golden Oldies' With Slug |publisher=HipHopDX.com |date=2020-03-26 |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/RAtheRuggedMan/status/1249719024340078593</ref>\n| title1          = All My Heroes Are Dead (The Introduction)\n| note1           = \n| extra1          = \n| length1         = 2:33\n| title2          = Legendary Loser\n| extra2          = [[Psycho Les]]\n| length2         = 4:21\n| title3          = Golden Oldies\n| note3           = featuring [[Atmosphere (music group)|Atmosphere]] and [[Eamon (singer)|Eamon]]\n| extra3          = [[The Kickdrums]]\n| length3         = 3:32\n| title4          = Wondering (How to Believe)\n| note4           = featuring [[David Myles (musician)|David Myles]]\n| extra4          = Classified\n| length4         = 4:01\n| title5          = Dragon Fire\n| note5           = featuring [[Ghostface Killah]], [[Kool G Rap]], [[Masta Killa]] and XX3EME\n| extra5          = Shroom\n| length5         = 4:36\n| title6          = All Systems Go\n| note6           = \n| extra6          = [[Michal Menert]]\n| length6         = 3:22\n| title7          = Cancelled Skit\n| note7           = Performed by [[Psalm One]] and Angel Davanport\n| extra7          = \n| length7         = 0:23\n| title8          = Angelic Boy\n| extra8          = The Kickdrums, [[Chris Conway (recording engineer)|Chris Conway]]\n| length8         = 4:15\n| title9          = Gotta Be Dope\n| note9           = featuring A-F-R-O and [[DJ Jazzy Jeff]]\n| extra9          = C